                  "level": 4,
                  "node_kind": "heading",
                  "heading_text": "More details",
                  "anchor_id": "more-details",
                  "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/debugging/#more-details",
                  "section_text_parts": [
                    "Let's say your file is named myapp.py .",
                    "If you run it with:",
                    "then the internal variable __name__ in your file, created automatically by Python, will have as value the string \"__main__\" .",
                    "So, the section:",
                    "will run.",
                    "This won't happen if you import that module (file).",
                    "So, if you have another file importer.py with:",
                    "in that case, the automatically created variable __name__ inside of myapp.py will not have the value \"__main__\" .",
                    "So, the line:",
                    "will not be executed."
                  ],
                  "section_text": "Let's say your file is named myapp.py .\n\nIf you run it with:\n\nthen the internal variable __name__ in your file, created automatically by Python, will have as value the string \"__main__\" .\n\nSo, the section:\n\nwill run.\n\nThis won't happen if you import that module (file).\n\nSo, if you have another file importer.py with:\n\nin that case, the automatically created variable __name__ inside of myapp.py will not have the value \"__main__\" .\n\nSo, the line:\n\nwill not be executed.",
