          "level": 2,
          "node_kind": "heading",
          "heading_text": "Run your code with your debugger",
          "anchor_id": "run-your-code-with-your-debugger",
          "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/debugging/#run-your-code-with-your-debugger",
          "section_text_parts": [
            "Because you are running the Uvicorn server directly from your code, you can call your Python program (your FastAPI application) directly from the debugger.",
            "For example, in Visual Studio Code, you can:",
            "- Go to the \"Debug\" panel.",
            "- \"Add configuration...\".",
            "- Select \"Python\"",
            "- Run the debugger with the option \" Python: Current File (Integrated Terminal) \".",
            "It will then start the server with your FastAPI code, stop at your breakpoints, etc.",
            "Here's how it might look:",
            "If you use Pycharm, you can:",
            "- Open the \"Run\" menu.",
            "- Select the option \"Debug...\".",
            "- Then a context menu shows up.",
            "- Select the file to debug (in this case, main.py ).",
            "It will then start the server with your FastAPI code, stop at your breakpoints, etc.",
            "Here's how it might look:"
          ],
          "section_text": "Because you are running the Uvicorn server directly from your code, you can call your Python program (your FastAPI application) directly from the debugger.\n\nFor example, in Visual Studio Code, you can:\n\n- Go to the \"Debug\" panel.\n\n- \"Add configuration...\".\n\n- Select \"Python\"\n\n- Run the debugger with the option \" Python: Current File (Integrated Terminal) \".\n\nIt will then start the server with your FastAPI code, stop at your breakpoints, etc.\n\nHere's how it might look:\n\nIf you use Pycharm, you can:\n\n- Open the \"Run\" menu.\n\n- Select the option \"Debug...\".\n\n- Then a context menu shows up.\n\n- Select the file to debug (in this case, main.py ).\n\nIt will then start the server with your FastAPI code, stop at your breakpoints, etc.\n\nHere's how it might look:",
          "section_inline_code": [
            "Python: Current File (Integrated Terminal)",
            "main.py"
          ],
